{"TopicId":146344,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Dry Center of Mass?","CreatedByName":"b0ss","CreatedById":164861,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T10:12:26Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"b0ss","CreatedById":164861,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T10:12:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know, to me it seems pretty important to have the Dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E show up in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E. Would be great for planning flight during different fuel levels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"r4pt0r","CreatedById":90471,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T10:15:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhile you can manually lower the tanks, that is very inconvenient.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nYeah adding a toggle on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E button for wet/dry loads would be nice. Supported.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mhoram","CreatedById":78756,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T10:33:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the moment you could use the mod \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-11x-rcs-build-aid-v081/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build Aid\u003C/a\u003E, which provides this functionality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T10:41:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. Dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E would be really nice to have.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T11:00:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222725275\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471860933\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002290471\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022r4pt0r\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, r4pt0r said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah adding a toggle on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E button for wet/dry loads would be nice. Supported.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly I\u0027d find it more useful to have both showing all the time, as \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build Aid does it. Being able to directly compare them is pretty handy, especially when building planes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, \u002B1 to this suggestion, it\u0027s really useful functionality.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T11:12:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes to this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T13:07:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d also like to see dry mass displayed in the stats tab, to make it quicker to calculate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E. I think dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E would be a very useful thing to see too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kerbart","CreatedById":78303,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T13:21:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222725278\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221471862034\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002278756\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mhoram\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, mhoram said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor the moment you could use the mod \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/33124-11x-rcs-build-aid-v081/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E Build Aid\u003C/a\u003E, which provides this functionality.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can\u0027t if you\u0027re on a console. That\u0027s one side effect of the console editions: \u201C\u003Cem\u003Ethere\u0027s a mod for that\u003C/em\u003E\u201D is becoming less of a catch-all response.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"b0ss","CreatedById":164861,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T13:37:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother good thing to have would be\u00A0separate \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u002BDCoM\u0027s for each stage (each toggleable, ofc).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-22T19:12:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes to this, and I agree that it would be better to be able to have both visible together.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"b0ss","CreatedById":164861,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T18:28:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA crewless center of mass would be nice as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T18:33:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222731193\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472236093\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164861\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022b0ss\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, b0ss said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA crewless center of mass would be nice as well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrew in pods don\u0027t have any mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-26T19:01:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222731207\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472236428\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrew in pods don\u0027t have any mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat brings up, though, that it\u0027d be nice to be able to toggle chairs as occupied or not in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-27T11:43:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222731241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472238068\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat brings up, though, that it\u0027d be nice to be able to toggle chairs as occupied or not in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003ESPH\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, Jeb, you can not have that seat. \u00A0That seat is for Bob. \u00A0Bob is stuck in space now. \u00A0We have to get him. \u00A0That\u0027s his seat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"b0ss","CreatedById":164861,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-27T11:53:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222731207\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472236428\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002212858\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Red Iron Crown\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Red Iron Crown said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCrew in pods don\u0027t have any mass.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally? I thought they did... does \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E fix that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Red Iron Crown","CreatedById":12858,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-27T12:06:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222732075\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472298801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164861\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022b0ss\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, b0ss said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReally? I thought they did... does \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E fix that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t think \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Ferram Aerospace Research (mod)\u0022\u003EFAR\u003C/abbr\u003E touches it. There\u0027s a setting in Physics.cfg that can make kerbals in pods have mass that is off by default, I believe Realism Overhaul turns it on. Possibly other mods too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-27T12:39:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes, I support this too. But,\u00A0being the demanding so and so that I am,\u00A0I want more.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027d like a master fuel slider that lets you drain the fuel (either all fuels, or just those selected) gradually, either across all stages or just for a single stage. That would let you see how the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E changes during flight. \u00A0For each tank the master slider would take whatever value you\u0027ve adjusted the fuel to as it\u0027s 100% value, so for example if you had two tanks; one completely full and one half full, then when you brought the slider down to half, the full tank would now have 50% and the half full one would be down to 25%. Then when you return the slider to full the fuel levels would be back to what you\u0027d set them to (one full and one half full).\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis is mostly for spaceplane design, I don\u0027t see it being as useful for rocket/landers and for spaceplanes if it altered the levels on\u00A0all stages that would be ok, but stage by stage control would be ideal. Ideally what I want is a mixing board type interface with a slider per stage and one master slider that changes all stages.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-27T12:47:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222732070\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022146344\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221472298239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105132\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022klgraham1013\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, klgraham1013 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, Jeb, you can not have that seat. \u00A0That seat is for Bob. \u00A0Bob is stuck in space now. \u00A0We have to get him. \u00A0That\u0027s his seat.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaha I meant for weight balancing only but that would be nice too \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheGuyNamedAlan","CreatedById":162058,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-28T09:11:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotally agreed. Dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E would help \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003Essto\u003C/abbr\u003E calculate if reentery with empty fuel tanks works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-28T12:10:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust gonna throw this mod suggestion out there for anyone who might benefit from it:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/130783-113-correctcol-v141-stock-aerodynamics-design-aid/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt fixes some errors in the stock \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator and also provides a super handy chart for comparing dry vs. wet mass control stability.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022oYei22M.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022380\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/oYei22M.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-28T12:10:43Z\u0022 title=\u002208/28/2016 12:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Firemetal","CreatedById":164725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-28T14:52:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd be able to see it in flight. Now THAT would be helpful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Justicier","CreatedById":89671,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-29T03:14:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEver since I saw its implementation in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E Build aid I thought for sure that it would become stock by now. Obviously not, therefore, I support the motion wholeheartedly. Very useful for aircraft/spaceplanes or designing an asymmetric rocket or Space Shuttle clone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}